channel.title: [RSCali] - Adding Grand Exchange [Warning Window]
channel.description:
Ok so I have been trying to add GE to the RSCali Base server and it is proving to be a pretty big pain in the ass -- which is why I made an account here finally lol.
So I have the interface up, I am sending the correct configs -- that I know of [1109, 1110, 1111, 1112, 1113, 1114]. I dont think that I need to send the 1115 or 1116 because Min and Max were removed from RuneScape to allow for the "Custom Price".
So I have it set up so you can click "buy" or "sell" and for whatever reason when you click "Sell" this is what it shows: [IMG]http://img809.imageshack.us/img809/2153/rspsge.png[/img]
I have tried modifying all config settings from 1109 - 1120. I have also tried making the current buy price [1111] higher than the current sell price [1114] -- but that also didn't work.
This is stalled development on my Grand Exchange lol and I just need some help. Also -- the current interface that I am using is [105].
Thanks for the future responses! :)
EDIT: To clear this up, I want that "Warning!" bullshit gone lol. I just need to know if anyone else knows how to remove that child component forever. Also -- it is part of the main Interface 105 so I cant just close out of the interface -- I think.
